{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JCjV6g14vgnczAwy3Pryzc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JJd1qo6J2fr4e82Q2B9JTD","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/agent_output/answer.json","content":"{\n  \"api_changes\": {\n    \"removed\": [\n      \"func FromContext(ctx context.Context) (md MD, ok bool) — deprecated shim present in grpc-go ≤v1.4.0, fully removed by v1.14.0\",\n      \"func NewContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context — deprecated shim present in grpc-go ≤v1.4.0, fully removed by v1.14.0\"\n    ],\n    \"added\": [\n      \"func NewIncomingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context — stores MD under mdIncomingKey{}; used server-side by gRPC runtime\",\n      \"func NewOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, md MD) context.Context — stores MD under mdOutgoingKey{}; used client-side before making calls\",\n      \"func FromIncomingContext(ctx context.Context) (MD, bool) — reads from mdIncomingKey{}; use in server handlers\",\n      \"func FromOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context) (MD, bool) — reads from mdOutgoingKey{}; use in client code\",\n      \"func AppendToOutgoingContext(ctx context.Context, kv ...string) context.Context — appends to existing outgoing metadata\",\n      \"func ValueFromIncomingContext(ctx context.Context, key string) []string — reads single key from incoming metadata\"\n    ],\n    \"description\": \"PR #1157 introduced separate context keys for incoming (server-received) and outgoing (client-sent) metadata, splitting the previously unified context key into mdIncomingKey{} and mdOutgoingKey{}. Before the split, a single context key held all metadata, so FromContext read whatever was in the context regardless of direction. After the split, incoming metadata (populated by the gRPC server transport when a request arrives) lives under mdIncomingKey{}, and outgoing metadata (populated by the client before a call) lives under mdOutgoingKey{}. The deprecated shims FromContext and NewContext were present in v1.4.0 but completely removed by v1.14.0. Critical behavioral consequence: any server-handler code that calls FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()) will ALWAYS return ok=false because the server transport populates only the incoming key — a silent runtime failure that compiles successfully.\"\n  },\n  \"affected_files\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"auth/store.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0 era)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"compile_error\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": false,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": null,\n      \"severity\": \"high\",\n      \"notes\": \"AuthInfoFromCtx calls metadata.FromContext(ctx) to extract the auth token. Compile error when grpc-go removes FromContext. Fix: metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx). Resolved in etcd v3.3.0.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0 era)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"compile_error\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": false,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": null,\n      \"severity\": \"high\",\n      \"notes\": \"Two call sites: newUnaryInterceptor and newStreamInterceptor both call metadata.FromContext to check MetadataRequireLeaderKey in server interceptors. Compile error when grpc-go removes FromContext. Fix: metadata.FromIncomingContext. Resolved in etcd v3.3.0.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"clientv3/client.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0 era)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.NewContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"compile_error\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": false,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": null,\n      \"severity\": \"high\",\n      \"notes\": \"Client-side: metadata.NewContext(ctx, md) sets the require-leader key before making a gRPC call. NewContext was a deprecated shim for NewOutgoingContext. Compile error when removed. Fix: metadata.NewOutgoingContext. Resolved in etcd v3.3.0.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0 era)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"compile_error\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": false,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": \"Reads stream.Context() metadata to check MetadataRequireLeaderKey in server handler\",\n      \"severity\": \"high\",\n      \"notes\": \"Server-stream Watch handler calls metadata.FromContext(stream.Context()). Compile error when removed. The migration to v3.3.0 replaced this with FromOutgoingContext (wrong) instead of FromIncomingContext (correct), introducing a silent regression.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/etcd-io/etcd (v3.3.0 through latest/v3.5.x)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromOutgoingContext (incorrect replacement for FromContext in server handler)\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"runtime_behavior\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": true,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": \"Server-side Watch handler calls metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()) to read MetadataRequireLeaderKey. In a gRPC server handler, stream.Context() has metadata stored under mdIncomingKey{} (not mdOutgoingKey{}), so FromOutgoingContext always returns ok=false. The require-leader enforcement block never executes.\",\n      \"severity\": \"critical\",\n      \"notes\": \"Code: `if md, ok := metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()); ok { v := md[rpctypes.MetadataRequireLeaderKey] ... }`. The condition is always false in a server context. The grpc proxy silently fails to enforce require-leader for Watch streams even when the client sends MetadataRequireLeaderKey. Present in v3.3.0, v3.4.x, v3.5.x, and latest. Correct fix: metadata.FromIncomingContext(stream.Context()).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/etcd-io/etcd (v3.3.0 through latest/v3.5.x)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromOutgoingContext (incorrect replacement for FromContext in server handler)\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"runtime_behavior\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": true,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": \"Server-side LeaseKeepAlive handler calls metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()) to check MetadataRequireLeaderKey. Same incorrect pattern as watch.go — always returns ok=false in server context.\",\n      \"severity\": \"critical\",\n      \"notes\": \"Same bug as proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go. LeaseKeepAlive require-leader enforcement in the grpc proxy is silently bypassed from v3.3.0 through latest. Correct fix: metadata.FromIncomingContext(stream.Context()).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/util.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/etcd-io/etcd (v3.3.0 through latest)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromIncomingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"none\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": false,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": \"Reads auth token from incoming context in getAuthTokenFromClient, then forwards via PerRPCCredentials (not raw metadata copy)\",\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"notes\": \"Correctly uses FromIncomingContext on the server side. Auth token forwarding uses proxyTokenCredential/PerRPCCredentials which is the proper pattern, not raw metadata copying.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"auth/store.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/etcd-io/etcd (v3.3.0 through latest)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromIncomingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"none\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": false,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": null,\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"notes\": \"AuthInfoFromCtx correctly uses FromIncomingContext to extract auth token from server-side context. Properly migrated from pre-v3.3.0 FromContext.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/etcd-io/etcd (v3.3.0 through latest)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromIncomingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"none\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": false,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": null,\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"notes\": \"Both unary and stream server interceptors correctly use FromIncomingContext to check MetadataRequireLeaderKey and API version. Properly migrated.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"clientv3/lease.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/etcd-io/etcd (v3.3.0 through latest)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromOutgoingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"none\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": false,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": null,\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"notes\": \"Client-side: closeRequireLeader reads FromOutgoingContext to identify keepalive leases with require-leader set. Correct usage — these are client-owned contexts.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"clientv3/watch.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/etcd-io/etcd (v3.3.0 through latest)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromOutgoingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"none\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": false,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": null,\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"notes\": \"Client-side: streamKeyFromCtx reads outgoing metadata to compute a stream deduplication key. Correct use of FromOutgoingContext in client context.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"server/etcdserver/cluster_util.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/etcd-io/etcd (v3.5.x / latest)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromIncomingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"none\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": true,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": \"Reads auth token fields from gRPC incoming metadata (FromIncomingContext) and forwards them as HTTP Authorization headers when proxying member-promote requests over HTTP. Intentional cross-protocol forwarding.\",\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"notes\": \"promoteMember reads incoming gRPC metadata (TokenFieldNameGRPC, TokenFieldNameSwagger) and sets them as HTTP headers. Correct API usage but fragile — any change to incoming metadata key names would silently drop auth token forwarding for HTTP-proxied requests.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"pkg/grpctesting/recorder.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/etcd-io/etcd (v3.5.x / latest)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromIncomingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"none\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": false,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": null,\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"notes\": \"Test infrastructure only. Records observed incoming metadata for test assertions.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"critical_forwarding_files\": [\n    \"proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go — uses FromOutgoingContext in server handler (WRONG: should be FromIncomingContext), silently never reads MetadataRequireLeaderKey; require-leader enforcement completely bypassed for Watch streams\",\n    \"proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go — same bug as watch.go for LeaseKeepAlive streams; require-leader enforcement silently bypassed\",\n    \"server/etcdserver/cluster_util.go — reads FromIncomingContext and forwards token as HTTP header (correct API usage, but fragile cross-protocol forwarding)\"\n  ],\n  \"source_files\": [\n    {\"path\": \"auth/store.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/client.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/util.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/lease.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/watch.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"server/etcdserver/cluster_util.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"pkg/grpctesting/recorder.go\"}\n  ],\n  \"error_chain\": [\n    \"grpc-go PR #1157 splits single metadata context key into mdIncomingKey{} (server-received) and mdOutgoingKey{} (client-sent)\",\n    \"Deprecated shims FromContext/NewContext added in v1.4.0 — compile succeeds but behavior changes\",\n    \"Shims fully removed by v1.14.0 — coreos/etcd code using FromContext/NewContext now fails to compile\",\n    \"etcd v3.3.0 migration replaces FromContext with FromOutgoingContext (wrong) in proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go and lease.go instead of FromIncomingContext\",\n    \"All subsequent etcd versions (v3.3.0–v3.5.x) carry silent runtime bug: MetadataRequireLeaderKey check never fires in Watch/LeaseKeepAlive proxy handlers\"\n  ],\n  \"trigger_conditions\": [\n    \"Upgrading grpc-go from ≤v1.4.0 to ≥v1.14.0 causes compile errors in pre-v3.3.0 coreos/etcd for: auth/store.go, etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go, clientv3/client.go, proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go\",\n    \"Any etcd version v3.3.0+ using the grpc proxy: clients sending MetadataRequireLeaderKey for Watch or LeaseKeepAlive streams will have the key silently ignored\",\n    \"gRPC server handler code calling metadata.FromOutgoingContext(ctx) where ctx comes from a server stream — always returns (nil, false)\"\n  ],\n  \"code_paths\": [\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/util.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"auth/store.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/client.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/lease.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/watch.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"server/etcdserver/cluster_util.go\"}\n  ],\n  \"ownership\": \"etcd gRPC proxy layer (proxy/grpcproxy/) — specifically the Watch and LeaseKeepAlive stream handlers and the server-side interceptor/auth subsystems\",\n  \"severity\": {\n    \"level\": \"critical\",\n    \"rationale\": \"Two silent runtime regressions exist in proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go and proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go from v3.3.0 through latest: the MetadataRequireLeaderKey require-leader enforcement is completely bypassed in the grpc proxy because FromOutgoingContext was incorrectly used instead of FromIncomingContext in server handlers. This means clients cannot rely on the grpc proxy to enforce leader-only reads for Watch or LeaseKeepAlive operations, potentially returning stale data from follower nodes while the client believes it has strong consistency guarantees. The compile errors from the API removal are mechanical and easy to fix; the silent behavior regression is the true danger.\"\n  },\n  \"grpc_go_version_details\": {\n    \"api_split_pr\": \"grpc-go PR #1157\",\n    \"deprecated_shims_present_until\": \"grpc-go v1.4.0\",\n    \"shims_fully_removed_by\": \"grpc-go v1.14.0\",\n    \"compile_error_versions\": \"coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0) when upgrading grpc-go past v1.4.0\",\n    \"runtime_regression_versions\": \"etcd v3.3.0 through latest (v3.5.17+)\"\n  }\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":161,"cache_read_input_tokens":22487,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":161},"output_tokens":38,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c6a61d1-0fa0-43c6-80f7-1a961d909727","uuid":"6c834d32-33f7-494d-9d0e-8ac2dd18c9d9"}
