rn\": \"Reads auth token fields from gRPC incoming metadata (FromIncomingContext) and forwards them as HTTP Authorization headers when proxying member-promote requests over HTTP. Intentional cross-protocol forwarding.\",\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"notes\": \"promoteMember reads incoming gRPC metadata (TokenFieldNameGRPC, TokenFieldNameSwagger) and sets them as HTTP headers. Correct API usage but fragile — any change to incoming metadata key names would silently drop auth token forwarding for HTTP-proxied requests.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"pkg/grpctesting/recorder.go\",\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/etcd-io/etcd (v3.5.x / latest)\",\n      \"old_api_uses\": [\"metadata.FromIncomingContext\"],\n      \"breakage_type\": \"none\",\n      \"is_metadata_forwarding\": false,\n      \"forwarding_pattern\": null,\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"notes\": \"Test infrastructure only. Records observed incoming metadata for test assertions.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"critical_forwarding_files\": [\n    \"proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go — uses FromOutgoingContext in server handler (WRONG: should be FromIncomingContext), silently never reads MetadataRequireLeaderKey; require-leader enforcement completely bypassed for Watch streams\",\n    \"proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go — same bug as watch.go for LeaseKeepAlive streams; require-leader enforcement silently bypassed\",\n    \"server/etcdserver/cluster_util.go — reads FromIncomingContext and forwards token as HTTP header (correct API usage, but fragile cross-protocol forwarding)\"\n  ],\n  \"source_files\": [\n    {\"path\": \"auth/store.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/client.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/util.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/lease.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/watch.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"server/etcdserver/cluster_util.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"pkg/grpctesting/recorder.go\"}\n  ],\n  \"error_chain\": [\n    \"grpc-go PR #1157 splits single metadata context key into mdIncomingKey{} (server-received) and mdOutgoingKey{} (client-sent)\",\n    \"Deprecated shims FromContext/NewContext added in v1.4.0 — compile succeeds but behavior changes\",\n    \"Shims fully removed by v1.14.0 — coreos/etcd code using FromContext/NewContext now fails to compile\",\n    \"etcd v3.3.0 migration replaces FromContext with FromOutgoingContext (wrong) in proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go and lease.go instead of FromIncomingContext\",\n    \"All subsequent etcd versions (v3.3.0–v3.5.x) carry silent runtime bug: MetadataRequireLeaderKey check never fires in Watch/LeaseKeepAlive proxy handlers\"\n  ],\n  \"trigger_conditions\": [\n    \"Upgrading grpc-go from ≤v1.4.0 to ≥v1.14.0 causes compile errors in pre-v3.3.0 coreos/etcd for: auth/store.go, etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go, clientv3/client.go, proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go\",\n    \"Any etcd version v3.3.0+ using the grpc proxy: clients sending MetadataRequireLeaderKey for Watch or LeaseKeepAlive streams will have the key silently ignored\",\n    \"gRPC server handler code calling metadata.FromOutgoingContext(ctx) where ctx comes from a server stream — always returns (nil, false)\"\n  ],\n  \"code_paths\": [\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"proxy/grpcproxy/util.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"auth/store.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/client.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/lease.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"clientv3/watch.go\"},\n    {\"path\": \"server/etcdserver/cluster_util.go\"}\n  ],\n  \"ownership\": \"etcd gRPC proxy layer (proxy/grpcproxy/) — specifically the Watch and LeaseKeepAlive stream handlers and the server-side interceptor/auth subsystems\",\n  \"severity\": {\n    \"level\": \"critical\",\n    \"rationale\": \"Two silent runtime regressions exist in proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go and proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go from v3.3.0 through latest: the MetadataRequireLeaderKey require-leader enforcement is completely bypassed in the grpc proxy because FromOutgoingContext was incorrectly used instead of FromIncomingContext in server handlers. This means clients cannot rely on the grpc proxy to enforce leader-only reads for Watch or LeaseKeepAlive operations, potentially returning stale data from follower nodes while the client believes it has strong consistency guarantees. The compile errors from the API removal are mechanical and easy to fix; the silent behavior regression is the true danger.\"\n  },\n  \"grpc_go_version_details\": {\n    \"api_split_pr\": \"grpc-go PR #1157\",\n    \"deprecated_shims_present_until\": \"grpc-go v1.4.0\",\n    \"shims_fully_removed_by\": \"grpc-go v1.14.0\",\n    \"compile_error_versions\": \"coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0) when upgrading grpc-go past v1.4.0\",\n    \"runtime_regression_versions\": \"etcd v3.3.0 through latest (v3.5.17+)\"\n  }\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012VTAN3FhoNMRZRjoxyh4hD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FMsUabBoq3xq9arxWYYvD1","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/analysis/IMPACT_REPORT.md","content":"# Impact Report: gRPC-Go Metadata Context Separation (PR #1157)\n\n## Breaking API Changes\n\ngRPC-Go PR #1157 split the previously unified metadata context key into two separate keys:\n\n| Old API | New API | Direction |\n|---------|---------|-----------|\n| `metadata.FromContext(ctx)` | `metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)` | Server handler reading received metadata |\n| `metadata.FromContext(ctx)` | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext(ctx)` | Client code reading metadata it set |\n| `metadata.NewContext(ctx, md)` | `metadata.NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md)` | Client code setting metadata before call |\n| _(new)_ | `metadata.NewIncomingContext(ctx, md)` | gRPC runtime populating server-side context |\n\n**Key behavioral change:** Before PR #1157, a single context key held all metadata. After the split:\n- `mdIncomingKey{}` — populated exclusively by the gRPC server transport when a request arrives\n- `mdOutgoingKey{}` — populated exclusively by client code before making a call\n\n**Consequence:** Calling `metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context())` inside a gRPC server handler **always returns `(nil, false)`** because the server transport only populates the incoming key. This is a silent runtime failure — the code compiles without errors.\n\n**Version timeline:**\n- Deprecated shims (`FromContext`, `NewContext`) present in grpc-go ≤ v1.4.0\n- Shims fully removed by grpc-go v1.14.0 (compile errors for callers)\n\n---\n\n## Affected etcd Files\n\n| File | Repo Era | Old API Used | Breakage Type | Severity |\n|------|----------|--------------|---------------|----------|\n| `auth/store.go` | coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0) | `metadata.FromContext` | **Compile error** | High |\n| `etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` | coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0) | `metadata.FromContext` (×2) | **Compile error** | High |\n| `clientv3/client.go` | coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0) | `metadata.NewContext` | **Compile error** | High |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` | coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0) | `metadata.FromContext` | **Compile error** | High |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0–latest | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext` (**wrong replacement**) | **Runtime behavior** | **Critical** |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0–latest | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext` (**wrong replacement**) | **Runtime behavior** | **Critical** |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/util.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0+ | `metadata.FromIncomingContext` | None (correct) | Low |\n| `auth/store.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0+ | `metadata.FromIncomingContext` | None (correct) | Low |\n| `etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0+ | `metadata.FromIncomingContext` | None (correct) | Low |\n| `clientv3/lease.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0+ | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext` | None (correct, client-side) | Low |\n| `clientv3/watch.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0+ | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext` | None (correct, client-side) | Low |\n| `server/etcdserver/cluster_util.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.5.x | `metadata.FromIncomingContext` | None (correct) | Medium |\n| `pkg/grpctesting/recorder.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.5.x | `metadata.FromIncomingContext` | None (test infra) | Low |\n\n---\n\n## Critical: Metadata Forwarding\n\n### proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go — CRITICAL REGRESSION (v3.3.0 through latest)\n\n**Pattern:** Server-side Watch handler incorrectly calls `metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context())` to check `MetadataRequireLeaderKey`.\n\n```go\n// WRONG — FromOutgoingContext always returns ok=false in a server handler\nif md, ok := metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()); ok {\n    v := md[rpctypes.MetadataRequireLeaderKey]\n    // This block NEVER executes\n}\n```\n\n**Impact:** The require-leader enforcement for Watch streams in the gRPC proxy is **completely bypassed**. Clients sending `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` believe they have strong consistency guarantees, but the proxy does not enforce leader-only reads — it may return stale data from follower nodes.\n\n**Root cause:** During the v3.3.0 migration from `metadata.FromContext`, developers chose `FromOutgoingContext` instead of `FromIncomingContext`. In a server handler, `stream.Context()` contains metadata under `mdIncomingKey{}`, not `mdOutgoingKey{}`.\n\n**Fix:** `metadata.FromIncomingContext(stream.Context())`\n\n---\n\n### proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go — CRITICAL REGRESSION (v3.3.0 through latest)\n\n**Pattern:** Identical bug in `LeaseKeepAlive` server-stream handler.\n\n```go\n// WRONG — same issue\nif md, ok := metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()); ok {\n    v := md[rpctypes.MetadataRequireLeaderKey]\n    // This block NEVER executes\n}\n```\n\n**Impact:** LeaseKeepAlive require-leader enforcement silently bypassed in the gRPC proxy. Lease keepalives may be processed by non-leader nodes even when the client requests leader-only behavior.\n\n**Fix:** `metadata.FromIncomingContext(stream.Context())`\n\n---\n\n### server/etcdserver/cluster_util.go — Correct but Fragile (v3.5.x)\n\n**Pattern:** `promoteMember` reads gRPC incoming metadata and forwards auth tokens as HTTP headers for cross-protocol proxying.\n\n```go\n// Correct usage — FromIncomingContext in server handler\nif md, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx); ok {\n    // Forward token fields as HTTP Authorization header\n}\n```\n\n**Risk:** Not a bug, but fragile. If incoming metadata key names (`TokenFieldNameGRPC`, `TokenFieldNameSwagger`) change, auth token forwarding silently breaks for HTTP-proxied member promote requests.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Category | Count |\n|----------|-------|\n| Compile errors (grpc-go upgrade past v1.14.0) | 4 files in coreos/etcd era |\n| Silent runtime regressions | 2 files (watch.go, lease.go) in v3.3.0–latest |\n| Correct API usage | 7 files |\n| **Critical metadata forwarding bugs** | **2 files** |\n\nThe compile errors from grpc-go removing `FromContext`/`NewContext` are straightforward to find and fix. The dangerous outcome is the **silent runtime regression** introduced during the v3.3.0 migration: `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` and `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` use `FromOutgoingContext` where `FromIncomingContext` is required, causing the require-leader feature to be silently non-functional in the gRPC proxy layer across all etcd versions from v3.3.0 through the current latest.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4384,"cache_read_input_tokens":22648,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4384},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c6a61d1-0fa0-43c6-80f7-1a961d909727","uuid":"ae736ded-940a-40f1-970a-8096a0509ec2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FMsUabBoq3xq9arxWYYvD1","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/analysis/IMPACT_REPORT.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c6a61d1-0fa0-43c6-80f7-1a961d909727","uuid":"62548ee5-3a23-472f-9dd6-902d5465a1a7","timestamp":"2026-04-01T01:28:25.282Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/analysis/IMPACT_REPORT.md","content":"# Impact Report: gRPC-Go Metadata Context Separation (PR #1157)\n\n## Breaking API Changes\n\ngRPC-Go PR #1157 split the previously unified metadata context key into two separate keys:\n\n| Old API | New API | Direction |\n|---------|---------|-----------|\n| `metadata.FromContext(ctx)` | `metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)` | Server handler reading received metadata |\n| `metadata.FromContext(ctx)` | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext(ctx)` | Client code reading metadata it set |\n| `metadata.NewContext(ctx, md)` | `metadata.NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md)` | Client code setting metadata before call |\n| _(new)_ | `metadata.NewIncomingContext(ctx, md)` | gRPC runtime populating server-side context |\n\n**Key behavioral change:** Before PR #1157, a single context key held all metadata. After the split:\n- `mdIncomingKey{}` — populated exclusively by the gRPC server transport when a request arrives\n- `mdOutgoingKey{}` — populated exclusively by client code before making a call\n\n**Consequence:** Calling `metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context())` inside a gRPC server handler **always returns `(nil, false)`** because the server transport only populates the incoming key. This is a silent runtime failure — the code compiles without errors.\n\n**Version timeline:**\n- Deprecated shims (`FromContext`, `NewContext`) present in grpc-go ≤ v1.4.0\n- Shims fully removed by grpc-go v1.14.0 (compile errors for callers)\n\n---\n\n## Affected etcd Files\n\n| File | Repo Era | Old API Used | Breakage Type | Severity |\n|------|----------|--------------|---------------|----------|\n| `auth/store.go` | coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0) | `metadata.FromContext` | **Compile error** | High |\n| `etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` | coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0) | `metadata.FromContext` (×2) | **Compile error** | High |\n| `clientv3/client.go` | coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0) | `metadata.NewContext` | **Compile error** | High |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` | coreos/etcd (pre-v3.3.0) | `metadata.FromContext` | **Compile error** | High |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0–latest | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext` (**wrong replacement**) | **Runtime behavior** | **Critical** |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0–latest | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext` (**wrong replacement**) | **Runtime behavior** | **Critical** |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/util.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0+ | `metadata.FromIncomingContext` | None (correct) | Low |\n| `auth/store.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0+ | `metadata.FromIncomingContext` | None (correct) | Low |\n| `etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0+ | `metadata.FromIncomingContext` | None (correct) | Low |\n| `clientv3/lease.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0+ | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext` | None (correct, client-side) | Low |\n| `clientv3/watch.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.3.0+ | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext` | None (correct, client-side) | Low |\n| `server/etcdserver/cluster_util.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.5.x | `metadata.FromIncomingContext` | None (correct) | Medium |\n| `pkg/grpctesting/recorder.go` | etcd-io/etcd v3.5.x | `metadata.FromIncomingContext` | None (test infra) | Low |\n\n---\n\n## Critical: Metadata Forwarding\n\n### proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go — CRITICAL REGRESSION (v3.3.0 through latest)\n\n**Pattern:** Server-side Watch handler incorrectly calls `metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context())` to check `MetadataRequireLeaderKey`.\n\n```go\n// WRONG — FromOutgoingContext always returns ok=false in a server handler\nif md, ok := metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()); ok {\n    v := md[rpctypes.MetadataRequireLeaderKey]\n    // This block NEVER executes\n}\n```\n\n**Impact:** The require-leader enforcement for Watch streams in the gRPC proxy is **completely bypassed**. Clients sending `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` believe they have strong consistency guarantees, but the proxy does not enforce leader-only reads — it may return stale data from follower nodes.\n\n**Root cause:** During the v3.3.0 migration from `metadata.FromContext`, developers chose `FromOutgoingContext` instead of `FromIncomingContext`. In a server handler, `stream.Context()` contains metadata under `mdIncomingKey{}`, not `mdOutgoingKey{}`.\n\n**Fix:** `metadata.FromIncomingContext(stream.Context())`\n\n---\n\n### proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go — CRITICAL REGRESSION (v3.3.0 through latest)\n\n**Pattern:** Identical bug in `LeaseKeepAlive` server-stream handler.\n\n```go\n// WRONG — same issue\nif md, ok := metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()); ok {\n    v := md[rpctypes.MetadataRequireLeaderKey]\n    // This block NEVER executes\n}\n```\n\n**Impact:** LeaseKeepAlive require-leader enforcement silently bypassed in the gRPC proxy. Lease keepalives may be processed by non-leader nodes even when the client requests leader-only behavior.\n\n**Fix:** `metadata.FromIncomingContext(stream.Context())`\n\n---\n\n### server/etcdserver/cluster_util.go — Correct but Fragile (v3.5.x)\n\n**Pattern:** `promoteMember` reads gRPC incoming metadata and forwards auth tokens as HTTP headers for cross-protocol proxying.\n\n```go\n// Correct usage — FromIncomingContext in server handler\nif md, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx); ok {\n    // Forward token fields as HTTP Authorization header\n}\n```\n\n**Risk:** Not a bug, but fragile. If incoming metadata key names (`TokenFieldNameGRPC`, `TokenFieldNameSwagger`) change, auth token forwarding silently breaks for HTTP-proxied member promote requests.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Category | Count |\n|----------|-------|\n| Compile errors (grpc-go upgrade past v1.14.0) | 4 files in coreos/etcd era |\n| Silent runtime regressions | 2 files (watch.go, lease.go) in v3.3.0–latest |\n| Correct API usage | 7 files |\n| **Critical metadata forwarding bugs** | **2 files** |\n\nThe compile errors from grpc-go removing `FromContext`/`NewContext` are straightforward to find and fix. The dangerous outcome is the **silent runtime regression** introduced during the v3.3.0 migration: `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` and `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` use `FromOutgoingContext` where `FromIncomingContext` is required, causing the require-leader feature to be silently non-functional in the gRPC proxy layer across all etcd versions from v3.3.0 through the current latest.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BE1n91vh9biFLuJUxJKy41","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both files written. Here's a summary of the findings:\n\n## Impact Analysis: gRPC-Go PR #1157 Metadata Split\n\n### Breaking API Changes\nThe PR split a single metadata context key into two:\n- `mdIncomingKey{}` → read via `FromIncomingContext` (server handlers)\n- `mdOutgoingKey{}` → read via `FromOutgoingContext` (client code)\n\nOld `FromContext`/`NewContext` shims were removed entirely by grpc-go v1.14.0.\n\n### Affected Files\n\n**Compile errors** (pre-v3.3.0 coreos/etcd, when upgrading grpc-go past v1.14.0):\n- `auth/store.go` — `metadata.FromContext` → must be `FromIncomingContext`\n- `etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` — two `metadata.FromContext` calls\n- `clientv3/client.go` — `metadata.NewContext` → must be `NewOutgoingContext`\n- `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` — `metadata.FromContext`\n\n### Critical: Silent Runtime Regressions (v3.3.0 through latest)\n\nThe most dangerous outcome is that the **v3.3.0 migration introduced new bugs** by replacing `FromContext` with the *wrong* new function:\n\n| File | Bug | Effect |\n|------|-----|--------|\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` | `FromOutgoingContext` used in server handler | `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` check **never fires** — require-leader completely bypassed for Watch streams |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` | Same | Require-leader bypassed for `LeaseKeepAlive` streams |\n\nIn a gRPC server handler, `stream.Context()` always stores metadata under `mdIncomingKey{}` — calling `FromOutgoingContext` there always returns `(nil, false)`. These bugs are present from **v3.3.0 through v3.5.17+** and would silently allow followers to serve Watch/LeaseKeepAlive responses when clients expect leader-only strong consistency.\n\n**Fix for both:** `metadata.FromIncomingContext(stream.Context())`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2058,"cache_read_input_tokens":27032,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2058},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c6a61d1-0fa0-43c6-80f7-1a961d909727","uuid":"7e42d046-38df-464f-a69b-0acf2102227f"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":446695,"duration_api_ms":402471,"num_turns":5,"result":"Both files written. Here's a summary of the findings:\n\n## Impact Analysis: gRPC-Go PR #1157 Metadata Split\n\n### Breaking API Changes\nThe PR split a single metadata context key into two:\n- `mdIncomingKey{}` → read via `FromIncomingContext` (server handlers)\n- `mdOutgoingKey{}` → read via `FromOutgoingContext` (client code)\n\nOld `FromContext`/`NewContext` shims were removed entirely by grpc-go v1.14.0.\n\n### Affected Files\n\n**Compile errors** (pre-v3.3.0 coreos/etcd, when upgrading grpc-go past v1.14.0):\n- `auth/store.go` — `metadata.FromContext` → must be `FromIncomingContext`\n- `etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` — two `metadata.FromContext` calls\n- `clientv3/client.go` — `metadata.NewContext` → must be `NewOutgoingContext`\n- `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` — `metadata.FromContext`\n\n### Critical: Silent Runtime Regressions (v3.3.0 through latest)\n\nThe most dangerous outcome is that the **v3.3.0 migration introduced new bugs** by replacing `FromContext` with the *wrong* new function:\n\n| File | Bug | Effect |\n|------|-----|--------|\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` | `FromOutgoingContext` used in server handler | `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` check **never fires** — require-leader completely bypassed for Watch streams |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` | Same | Require-leader bypassed for `LeaseKeepAlive` streams |\n\nIn a gRPC server handler, `stream.Context()` always stores metadata under `mdIncomingKey{}` — calling `FromOutgoingContext` there always returns `(nil, false)`. These bugs are present from **v3.3.0 through v3.5.17+** and would silently allow followers to serve Watch/LeaseKeepAlive responses when clients expect leader-only strong consistency.\n\n**Fix for both:** `metadata.FromIncomingContext(stream.Context())`","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"9c6a61d1-0fa0-43c6-80f7-1a961d909727","total_cost_usd":0.7057768500000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14854,"cache_read_input_tokens":102751,"output_tokens":8103,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":14854,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":1649,"outputTokens":18972,"cacheReadInputTokens":641087,"cacheCreationInputTokens":59713,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.7057768500000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"ffdf4342-2e11-4511-876e-3ee85bffad66"}
